The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                                        
	New Delhi: Australian hockey legend Ric Charlesworth feels that, going by the tradition, India are one of the favourites to lift the hockey World Cup that gets underway from February 28. I believe there are at least half-a-dozen teams who are capable of winning the tournament... But when you look at the history of such tournaments, the home team always does very well, the former India technical director said.      
	WTA demand  
	Melbourne: The head of the WTA, Stacey Allaster, wants changes to certain anti-doping rules for women tennis players, notably the stringent whereabouts rule that initially led to a one-year ban for Yanina Wickmayer.  
	T20 qualifier  
	Calcutta: Eight teams  Ireland, Scotland, Afghanistan, US, the Netherlands, Kenya, Canada and UAE  will fight it out in the ICC World T20 qualifier, which will be held in the United Arab Emirates (UAE) from February 9-13. The matches will be played in Dubai and Abu Dhabi.  
	Chess meet  
	Gibraltar: Koneru Humpy defeated fellow Indian Eesha Karavade while Sandipan Chanda was held by local Michael Hoffmann in the third round of the Gibtelecom Masters chess tournament.     
	Calcutta: The regional security manager of the ICC rsquo;s Anti-Corruption and Safety Unit (ACSU), Col Nuruddin Khawaja, passed away in Lahore on Friday morning.      
	Wellington: Former Australia Test batsman Darren Lehmann is among those in contention for the post of New Zealand coach. The New Zealand board met in Christchurch on Friday and said the new coach would be named Saturday.        
	Rome: The Italian Olympic Committee provisionally suspended Fiorentinas Adrian Mutu for alleged drugs use on Friday and revealed that the Romania striker had failed a second dope test. It was revealed Thursday that Mutu had given a positive sample for the same drug on Jan. 10. Traces of appetite suppressant sibutramin were found in samples Mutu gave on Jan. 20.                                                                                                                                                      
